@node about "About Play HIP"

   Play HIP is a little arexx script to play modules from DOpus 5 with
Hippo Player.

@endnode
@node requirements Requirements

You need following things to use Play HIP.      

- DOpus 5.? (I started the project in 1995 and script hasn't change
             much so it should work even with early version)
- Hippo Player 1.? (same goes for here)
- Installed ARexx system                                

@endnode

@node install Install

First of all you have to copy PlayMod_HIP.dopus5 to DOpus5:arexx/
Then you must edit the script a little. Change the first line of 
script after the comments, the one that says:
HIPPO='HD1:Music/HippoPlayer/HIP'   /* Path for your hippo*/
Just replace the path with the one you use.

After that you may call it from the 'Double-click' function for
the 'Music module' filetype. Enter the following command:
<ARexx> DOpus5:arexx/PlayMod_HIP.dopus5 {f}

@endnode
@node usage "Usage"

    After you have install it just double click modules and rest should be
quite self explanatory.

@endnode
